U.K. stocks rose, pushing the
benchmark FTSE 100 Index higher for a fourth day. The gauge
climbed 19.23, or 0.3 percent, to 5,721.60 as of 11:48 a.m. in
 London .  Barclays Plc surged 6.8 percent, Lloyds Banking Group Plc
gained 4.4 percent and Royal Bank of Scotland Group Plc advanced
5 percent.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
